      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Isotropic linear-elastic titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) model with frictional Coulomb contact (mu=0.3) at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces; geometric nonlinearity (large-displacement) enabled. Model form justified by prior literature and material data sheet.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V exhibits linear-elastic behavior up to yield under F1717 loading rates. Geometric nonlinearity is necessary and enabled. Contact friction coefficient validated against independent tribology data for titanium-on-titanium. Model form is appropriate for the COU and meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (E=114 GPa, nu=0.33, Sy=880 MPa) sourced from certified material test reports for the production Ti-6Al-4V lot; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of production screws (n=5 per batch).",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and Poisson ratio taken from certified material test reports accompanying the implant lot. Screw and rod geometry digitized from CMM measurements; dimensional variability across n=5 units is <0.5% for all critical dimensions. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (500 samples); QoI sensitivity to E is dominant but within bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
