      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical performance endpoints and regulatory submission requirements for spinal fixation devices.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness predicts load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force is the primary fatigue-life surrogate; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption relevant to trauma scenarios. All three QoIs are cited in FDA guidance for spinal pedicle screw systems and directly support the 510(k) submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
