      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities replicate the COU geometry, material, loading, and boundary conditions to the extent achievable in a bench setting; deviations from in vivo conditions are documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 is the accepted surrogate for in vivo spinal loading for regulatory purposes. The validation construct geometry is identical to the clinical implant. Deviations from in vivo conditions (absence of bone, simplified loading axis) are consistent with regulatory expectations and bounded by sensitivity analyses. Validation activities are sufficiently relevant to the COU."
